Package org.neo4j.internal.batchimport

Class RelationshipGroupDefragmenter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.RelationshipGroupDefragmenter
  • public class RelationshipGroupDefragmenter
extends Object
    Defragments RelationshipGroupRecord so that they end up sequential per node in the group store. There's one constraint which is assumed to be true here: any relationship group that we see in the store for any given owner must have a lower type than any previous group encountered for that node, i.e. all next pointers must be either NULL or lower than the group id at hand. When this is true, and the defragmenter verifies this constraint, the groups will be reversed so that types are instead ascending and groups are always co-located.
